Package cs1302.ce13

Class Container<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • cs1302.ce13.Container<T>
  • public class Container<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a container for objects of type Object Each container has associated with it a set of properties. Within this documentation, a property that is referred to as set is assumed to refer to some object, and a property that is unset is assumed to contain the value null. Here is the full list of associated properties:
    • contents- a reference to an associated object of type Object; and
    • next - a reference to another Container object.

    Conditions for contents Property

    The contents property is not allowed to be unset. This condition is enforced by the container's constructors and associated setter methods.

    Conditions for next Property

    The next property may be set or unset. Users of this container may use verbeage such as "this container does not refer to another container" when this property is unset.
